stories: This paper aims to categorize multilingual and plurilingual electronic dictionaries and lexical resources, establishing criteria for a typology-based taxonomy. One goal is to differentiate lexicographic tools, such as dictionaries, from platforms and websites, and identify resources by their prototype degree. The paper will provide detailed descriptions of the resources, proposing parameters and typological frameworks to define and distinguish multilingual dictionaries, portals, and other electronic resources. It will also explore and critically examine the focus of multilingual and plurilingual lexicography.
